UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee v. Felipe Sebastian CHAN-GUTIERREZ, Defendant-Appellant. No. 09-40176

Conference Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Oct. 20, 2009. *994James Lee Turner, Assistant U.S. Attorney, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Houston, TX, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Marjorie A. Meyers, Federal Public Defender, Federal Public Defender’s Office, Southern District of Texas, Houston, TX, for Defendant-Appellant. Before WIENER, BENAVIDES, and STEWART, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM: *

The Federal Public Defender appointed to represent Felipe Sebastian Chan-Gutierrez has moved for leave to withdraw and has filed a brief in accordance with Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Chan-Gutierrez has not filed a response. Our independent review of the record and counsel’s brief discloses no nonfrivolous issue for appeal. Accordingly, counsel’s motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities herein, and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
